        "title": "feat(talk): add macOS realtime relay mode",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- add a provider-neutral macOS Talk realtime relay path backed by `talk.session.*` gateway RPCs\n- require explicit `talk.realtime.mode = realtime` plus `talk.realtime.transport = gateway-relay` before native macOS/Android Talk enters the realtime relay path\n- keep the existing native STT/TTS fallback when realtime relay config is missing or uses another transport\n- deliver OpenClaw brain/finalizer results back to the active realtime Talk session through a Talk-specific final-speech side channel\n- require realtime providers to implement `speakText` for final speech; do not emulate final speech by sending provider-visible user messages\n- parse structured Talk finals so the voice layer speaks only the `response`/`spokenText` field\n- mirror realtime final-speech state to the configured HUD endpoint as best-effort status\n- preserve typed relay tool payload/result values at the `AnyCodable` boundary\n- keep generic `chat.send` request/schema semantics unchanged; the prior `runtimePromptContext` request-field approach has been removed\n\n## Validation\n\n- `git diff --check`\n- PR-head diff scan for `runtimePromptContext`, `RuntimePromptContext`, and `chat.send.runtime` in the chat-send/protocol surface: no matches after `6a6e08cc103e`\n- `/private/tmp/openclaw-pnpm-bin/pnpm tsgo:core`\n- `/private/tmp/openclaw-pnpm-bin/pnpm tsgo:core:test`\n- `PATH=/private/tmp/openclaw-pnpm-bin:$PATH /private/tmp/openclaw-pnpm-bin/pnpm build:strict-smoke`\n- `/private/tmp/openclaw-pnpm-bin/node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run --config test/vitest/vitest.gateway.config.ts src/gateway/talk-final-hud-mirror.test.ts src/gateway/talk-realtime-relay.test.ts src/gateway/talk-realtime-chat-final.test.ts src/gateway/server-methods/chat.error-broadcast.test.ts src/gateway/server-chat.agent-events.test.ts`: 12 files, 158 tests passed\n- `/private/tmp/openclaw-pnpm-bin/node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run --config test/vitest/vitest.gateway.config.ts src/gateway/server.chat.gateway-server-chat-b.test.ts`: 34 tests passed\n- `swift test --package-path apps/shared/OpenClawKit --filter TalkPromptBuilderTests`: 4 tests passed\n- `swift test --package-path apps/macos --filter TalkModeGatewayConfigTests`: 4 tests passed after resetting stale SwiftPM artifacts and re-fetching cached Sparkle artifacts\n- `node /Users/tim/JSI/GIT/openclaw/dist/index.js health --json`: `ok: true`, no plugin errors\n- `node /Users/tim/JSI/GIT/openclaw/dist/index.js gateway status --json`: gateway `2026.6.2`, loopback RPC `ok: true`, `admin_capable`\n\nNot run:\n\n- Android Gradle unit test: blocked locally because no Android SDK is configured (`ANDROID_HOME` unset and no `apps/android/local.properties`).\n\n## Real Behavior Proof\n\n**Behavior addressed:** native Talk should only enter realtime relay when explicitly configured for `gateway-relay`; OpenClaw final text should be delivered through the active realtime Talk provider as final speech; final speech delivery should not add a new `chat.send` request field or route provider TTS through a fake user message.\n\n**PR-head proof available on this machine:**\n\n```text\n$ git rev-parse --short=12 HEAD\n6a6e08cc103e\n\n$ security find-identity -p codesigning -v\n0 valid identities found\n\n$ codesign --verify --strict --verbose=2 apps/macos/.build/arm64-apple-macosx/debug/OpenClaw\napps/macos/.build/arm64-apple-macosx/debug/OpenClaw: valid on disk\napps/macos/.build/arm64-apple-macosx/debug/OpenClaw: satisfies its Designated Requirement\n\n$ codesign -dv --verbose=4 apps/macos/.build/arm64-apple-macosx/debug/OpenClaw\nSignature=adhoc\nCDHash=d90284ee02e3fa2bd9e9af1d7c92957461d091ef\n```\n\nThe PR-head macOS package compiles and the SwiftPM-built executable verifies as ad-hoc signed. This machine has no valid Developer ID signing identity, so I cannot honestly claim a Developer ID signed PR-head app bundle or notarized runtime proof from this workstation.\n\n**Live runtime proof available on this machine:**\n\n```text\n$ node /Users/tim/JSI/GIT/openclaw/dist/index.js health --json\nok: true\nplugins.errors: []\ndefaultAgentId: brain\n\n$ node /Users/tim/JSI/GIT/openclaw/dist/index.js gateway status --json\ngateway.version: 2026.6.2\nrpc.ok: true\nrpc.capability: admin_capable\n```\n\n**What remains for maintainer/media proof:** a signed PR-head macOS app run showing relay session creation, microphone audio forwarding, assistant output audio playback, cancel/barge-in, omitted-transport fallback, and clean visible transcript text. The code now emits the provider-neutral relay markers needed for that capture, but this workstation cannot provide Developer ID signed app proof.\n",
